  15,53,"The Messenger from the Angels said: Do not be afraid! We will tell you something that will make you glad. You are going to have a son with great knowledge."
  15,56,"Abraham said: Does anyone despair from the mercy of his Lord but those who have deviated from Allahâ€™s straight path?!"
  15,57,"Abraham said: What is the matter that has brought you - O Messengers - from Allah?"
  15,59,"Except the family of Lot and the believers that follow him for they will not be included in the destruction and We will save them all from it."
  15,61,"When the Messengers from the Angels came to the family of Lot in the form of men."
  15,63,"The Messengers from the Angels said to Lot: Do not fear! We have brought to you - O Lot - the destructive punishment that your people have doubts about."
  15,65,"So travel with your family after a portion of the night has passed. Travel behind them and let none of you look back to see what happens to them. Proceed to where Allah has instructed you to go."
  15,69,"Fear Allah by leaving this indecent behaviour and do not humiliate me by this heinous act of yours."
  15,70,"His people said to him: Did we not forbid you from hosting anyone? One who provides a warning has in effect excused himself for taking someone to account for not abiding by it."